The paper proposes a multi-sensor fusion approach for localization of capsule endoscopy robots, which involves robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques. The use of a recurrent neural network for learning a non-linear kinematic model suggests a machine learning (cs.LG) component. The paper also discusses the detection and handling of sensor failures, which involves control systems (cs.SY) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques.
